<p>Pakistan shut multiple crossings with Afghanistan after overnight firefights along the frontier, saying Afghan troops opened fire on its border posts late Saturday and that Pakistan responded with gun and artillery fire [reuters.com#1]. Afghanistan’s Taliban administration called the attacks “retaliatory” for Pakistani airstrikes earlier in the week and claimed its forces killed 58 Pakistani soldiers and seized posts, a figure not confirmed by Islamabad [thehindu.com#1][bbc.com#1][ft.com#1][abcnews.go.com#1][france24.com#1][aljazeera.com#1]. Pakistani officials said several Afghan border posts were destroyed in counterstrikes, and reported that exchanges were mostly over by Sunday morning, though intermittent gunfire continued in Pakistan’s Kurram area [reuters.com#1]. The closures affect</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/UVwAXl_7UTXJjg47l-nJ6DDPflpxQ0--V-QRJrSD0d-VyuQi5jtjjJ2b1qK-uZEJNCn_dxSmtLLBFOCM6PKj9Fq_qrrgVCykuoaeUOBLNwn1RcDmRvvZbedSQvcLUJ-2MAPeTUwUC0R0gxTk6OXbPl25OtfFwgO75NiV4pSoU5UxEN-1PWk41Y5FfDwbIPdvw8SUy63t3-HG4vG_tPvxFQuPpqHMdSGl5HfADi-maWO7KFVouH1OWu8zl6km' alt='A Pakistani soldier stands guard along the Pakistan–Afghanistan border (file photo).' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Border closures: Pakistan closed Torkham and Chaman plus Kharlachi, Angoor Adda, and Ghulam Khan crossings following the exchanges of fire [reuters.com#1].</li><li>Casualty claims: Afghan authorities said 58 Pakistani soldiers were killed in &#x27;retaliatory&#x27; operations; Pakistan has not confirmed these numbers [thehindu.com#1][bbc.com#1][ft.com#1][abcnews.go.com#1][france24.com#1][aljazeera.com#1].</li><li>Posts targeted: Taliban officials said they captured three Pakistani border posts, while Pakistani officials said they destroyed several Afghan posts in response [thehindu.com#2][scmp.com#1][reuters.com#1][dw.com#1].</li><li>Trigger context: Kabul framed the attacks as retaliation for Pakistani airstrikes in the Afghan capital on Thursday targeting a Pakistani Taliban (TTP) leader, which Islamabad has not officially acknowledged [reuters.com#1][theguardian.com#1].</li><li>Current status: By Sunday morning, Pakistani officials said the exchanges were mostly over, though intermittent gunfire persisted in Kurram district [reuters.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>There is no kind of threat in any part of Afghanistan&#x27;s territory - Zabihullah Mujahid</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Afghanistan’s Ministry of Defence: Says its &#x27;retaliatory&#x27; cross-border attacks killed 58 Pakistani soldiers and seized posts. (<a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cgmzmn4971zo'>BBC</a>)</li><li>Pakistan security officials: Say the military responded &#x27;with full force&#x27; to firing from Afghanistan. (<a href='https://www.abc.net.au/news/2025-10-12/afghanistan-taliban-pakistan-border-fight-air-strike/105882450'>ABC News (Australia)</a>)</li><li>Pakistan (officials): Report that several Afghan border posts were destroyed in retaliatory attacks and that border crossings were closed. (<a href='https://www.reuters.com/world/asia-pacific/pakistan-closes-border-with-afghanistan-following-exchanges-fire-2025-10-12/'>Reuters</a>)</li><li>Taliban administration: Denies any internal security threat and says its operation concluded at midnight. (<a href='https://www.reuters.com/world/asia-pacific/pakistan-closes-border-with-afghanistan-following-exchanges-fire-2025-10-12/'>Reuters</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/afghanistan-claims-many-pakistani-soldiers-killed-in-clashes-border-closed/article70154653.ece'>Afghanistan claims 58 Pakistani soldiers killed in clashes; border closed</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.abc.net.au/news/2025-10-12/afghanistan-taliban-pakistan-border-fight-air-strike/105882450'>Afghan Taliban, Pakistani soldiers fight along border after Kabul air strike</a> - abc.net.au</li><li><a href='https://www.rferl.org/a/pakistan-afghan-tali